      • onStatusChange

        void onStatusChange(@NonNull
                    SensorDefinition sensorDefinition,

                    SensorStatus sensorStatus)
        Called when the connection status of the sensor changes. Note: The callback will be executed on the original caller's thread.

      • onDataReceived

                    SensorDefinition sensorDefinition,

      • onError

        void onError(@NonNull
             SensorDefinition sensorDefinition,
             @NonNull
             java.util.Set<java.lang.String> errors)
        Called when an error prevents the sensor from functioning. If the error is resolved the sensor will attempt to reconnect. Note: The callback will be executed on the original caller's thread.

      • onFailure

        void onFailure(@NonNull
               SensorDefinition sensorDefinition,
               @NonNull
               java.util.Set<java.lang.String> failures)
        Called when the connection fails due to something that cannot be resolved. No further callbacks will be made. Note: The callback will be executed on the original caller's thread.
